  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Responding to the increased risk of gender violence in El Salvador due to COVID</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This action proposes an intervention focused on responding to the main needs of women at risk and victims of gender violence. The three pillars of action will be: 1) Basic and protection needs: delivery of unconditional cash transfer for female victims that allows them access to essential items as well as economic means for their self -protection.  2) Provide access to the necessary information related to the prevention of gender -based violence and the means of referral to response and protection services. 3) Psychosocial support to people at risk and victims of gender violence: capacities will be strengthened for psychologists to give psychosocial and crisis support to women and adolescents.</narrative>
  </description>
